comment_regular_data.body:
> But why is this a problem?

Ignoring SIGWINCH in that case would regress https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/23411. That said, we could do:

```
if (tui->resize_events_enabled) {
  tui_set_size(tui, tui->width, tui->height);
  return;
}
```

which would force a UI refresh without having to check the current terminal dimensions.
